body: "## Context\n2026-07-04 sandbox review: installing pm-kanban registers the Card item type, but its cards/ folder is not created, so pm health returns top-level ok:false (warn-severity storage check) until the user re-runs pm init. The remediation hint is correct but the install should self-heal.\n\n## Approach\nAfter successful package install/activation, scaffold storage folders for every newly registered item type (same code path pm init uses). Declarative installs already do this when activation succeeds — reuse that scaffolding for package installs. Note pm-3wsi covers the adjacent case where FAILED activation skips scaffolding with a misleading report; this item is the success-path gap.\n\n## Definition of done\nFresh sandbox: install pm-kanban → pm health ok:true immediately, cards/ exists; spec asserts type-folder scaffolding for package installs; no regression for extension types with custom directories."
